===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|crepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|crēopan||to creep, crawl}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*kreupaną||to twist, creep}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*ger-||to turn, wind}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|krippe|lang=fy}}, {{term|krûpe|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|frs|-}} {{term|crjippa||to creep|lang=frs}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|krepen|lang=nds}}, {{term|krupen|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|kruipen||to creep, crawl|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|kriefen||to creep|lang=gmh}}, Danish {{term|krybe||to creep|lang=da}}, Norwegian {{term|krype||to creep|lang=no}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|krypa||to creep, crawl|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|krjúpa||to stoop|lang=is}}.

