{{en-verb|creeps|creeping|'''[[crept]]''', '''[[creeped]]''', or obsolete '''[[crope]]'''|'''[[crept]]''', '''[[creeped]]''', or archaic '''[[cropen]]'''}}

# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To move slowly with the [[abdomen]] close to the ground.
#: ''Lizards and snakes '''crept''' over the ground.''
#* '''1922''', {{w|Margery Williams}}, ''{{w|The Velveteen Rabbit}}''
#*: One evening, while the Rabbit was lying there alone, watching the ants that ran to and fro between his velvet paws in the grass, he saw two strange beings '''creep''' out of the tall bracken near him.
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} Of [[plant]]s, to grow across a surface rather than upwards.
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To move slowly and quietly in a particular direction.
#: ''He tried to '''creep''' past the guard without being seen.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To make small gradual changes, usually in a particular direction.
#: ''Prices have been '''creeping''' up all year.''

